{#- PLAINLY → prose -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acct-kpi-plainly" style="padding-top:8px;">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">In one paragraph</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">KPI &amp; management reporting, plainly.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p><strong>KPI and management reporting</strong> is the practice of identifying the small set of numbers that actually drive a business and reporting them on a regular cadence in a form leaders can act on. It goes beyond standard financial statements to track the metrics &mdash; margin, cash conversion, utilization, customer or unit economics &mdash; that explain why the numbers move and what to do next.</p>
      <p>The common failure is tracking dozens of metrics and acting on none; the fix is a focused set, often five to ten KPIs, that ties to the decisions you actually make, with both leading and lagging indicators. TechBrot&rsquo;s <a href="/quickbooks/proadvisor-team/">Certified ProAdvisors</a> build this on top of your <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/?intent=bookkeeping">accurate books</a> and deliver it monthly with plain-language commentary &mdash; board- and lender-ready when you need it. It&rsquo;s <a href="/accounting/advisory/?intent=advisory">advisory</a>, not bookkeeping or tax, and only as good as the books underneath it. Independent ProAdvisor firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- SIGNALS → r-2 of dc-card (sand) -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="acct-kpi-signals" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">When KPI reporting earns its keep</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">If any of these sound familiar, the answer is yes.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:68ch;">Most owners reach for management reporting when the numbers they have aren&rsquo;t answering the questions they&rsquo;re asking.</p>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for s in signals %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{{ s.opener | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ s.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- INCLUDED → r-3 of dc-card with num -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acct-kpi-included">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">What&rsquo;s included</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">What KPI &amp; management reporting actually delivers.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Scoped to your business and stage, reported on a cadence that matches how you make decisions.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for c in included %}
      <div class="dc-card"><p class="num" style="font-family:'Spline Sans Mono',monospace;font-size:12px;color:var(--color-accent);margin:0 0 4px;">{{ c.num }}</p><h3>{{ c.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ c.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- INDICATORS → vs comparison table (.cmp), plain-text cells (sand) -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="acct-kpi-indicators" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Leading vs lagging</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">The two halves of a KPI set that works.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Lagging metrics confirm where you&rsquo;ve been; leading metrics let you steer before results land. A useful set carries both. The metrics below are representative examples, not a fixed list.</p>
    <table class="cmp">
      <caption class="sr-only">Lagging indicators compared with leading indicators</caption>
      <thead><tr><th scope="col">Dimension</th><th scope="col">Lagging indicator</th><th scope="col" class="us">Leading indicator</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        {%- for r in indicatorTable %}
        <tr><th scope="row" data-col="Dimension">{{ r.dim | safe }}</th>
          <td data-col="Lagging indicator">{{ r.lagging | safe }}</td>
          <td class="us" data-col="Leading indicator">{{ r.leading | safe }}</td>
        </tr>
        {%- endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

{#- METRICS → r-3 of dc-card with eyebrow -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acct-kpi-metrics">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Industry &amp; role-specific metrics</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">The numbers your industry actually runs on.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">A generic dashboard measures everyone the same way and helps no one. We define the metrics that match how your business actually makes money. These are representative examples of the patterns we build for &mdash; the real set is defined with you.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for m in metricsByIndustry %}
      <div class="dc-card"><p class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:8px;">{{ m.tag | safe }}</p><h3>{{ m.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ m.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- PROCESS → process-grid (sand) -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="acct-kpi-process" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">How it works</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">From the right metrics to a report you&rsquo;ll actually use.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 32px;max-width:68ch;">Every KPI engagement follows the same four-phase rhythm &mdash; built on books that are accurate first.</p>
    <div class="process-grid">
      {%- for s in cadence %}
      <div class="process-step"><div class="process-step__n{% if loop.last %} process-step__n--done{% endif %}">{{ s.num | upper }}{% if loop.last %} &check;{% endif %}</div><h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3><p>{{ s.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- RHYTHM → r-3 of dc-card with eyebrow -#}
