{#- ADVISORY → prose (sand) -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="acct-kpi-advisory" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Beyond the report</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">Knowing the numbers is step one. Acting on them is the point.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>A good KPI report makes the right questions obvious: margin is slipping &mdash; where? Utilization is down &mdash; which team? Cash conversion is stretching &mdash; why? Seeing it clearly is the start; deciding what to do is the work that actually moves the business.</p>
      <p>For owners who want that judgment on an ongoing basis, KPI reporting is one piece of a broader <strong>advisory</strong> relationship &mdash; alongside <a href="/accounting/advisory/cash-flow-management/?intent=cash-flow">cash flow management</a>, budgeting, and strategy &mdash; up to a <a href="/accounting/advisory/fractional-cfo/?intent=fractional-cfo">fractional CFO</a> who owns the numbers with you. This is advisory work: we coordinate with your CPA for anything requiring a license, and we don&rsquo;t provide tax filing, audit, or assurance. As automation handles the routine, this interpretation layer is where the real value now lives.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

